.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE-EXPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource\-export \- Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource export [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.PP
Use this when you need a local datasource bundle for later inspection, diff, or import.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-export\-dir
target directory for the export tree.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
export one explicit Grafana org.
.TP
.B \-\-all\-orgs
export each visible org into per\-org subdirectories. Requires Basic auth.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
replace existing files.
.TP
.B \-\-without\-datasource\-provisioning
skip the provisioning variant.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
preview what would be written.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.EX
grafana-util datasource export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --export-dir ./datasources --overwrite
.EE
.PP
Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.EX
grafana-util datasource export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --all-orgs --export-dir ./datasources --overwrite
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-datasource\fR(1)
